{
  "version": 2,
  "builds": [
    {
      "src": "api/pln-inquiry.py",
      "use": "@vercel/python"
    }
  ],
  "routes": [
    {
      "src": "/api/(.*)",
      "dest": "/api/$1"
    },
    {
      "src": "/(.*)",
      "dest": "/$1"
    }
  ]
}
```

**Why This Works:**

- Vercel will automatically serve static files from your root directory
- The simplified routing configuration lets Vercel handle static assets naturally
- Your Python API routes are still protected with the first route rule

**Additional Recommendations:**

1. **Add a `public` directory (optional but cleaner):**
```
   public/
   ├── listriki2025.html
   ├── checklistbulanan.html
   ├── datakaryawan.html
   └── ... (other HTML files)
   css/
   js/
   api/
